      <title class="- topic/title " xtrc="title:2;16:14" xtrf="file:/C:/Git/dita/specification/common/reuse-w-lwdita/reuse-section.dita">Usage information</title>
      <p class="- topic/p " xtrc="p:1;17:10" xtrf="file:/C:/Git/dita/specification/common/reuse-w-lwdita/reuse-section.dita">Multiple <xmlelement class="+ topic/keyword markup-d/markupname xml-d/xmlelement " xtrc="xmlelement:3;17:31" xtrf="file:/C:/Git/dita/specification/common/reuse-w-lwdita/reuse-section.dita">section</xmlelement> elements within a single topic do not represent a
        hierarchy, but rather peer divisions of that topic. Sections cannot be nested.</p>
      <note class="- topic/note " xtrc="note:1;19:13" xtrf="file:/C:/Git/dita/specification/common/reuse-w-lwdita/reuse-section.dita">For maximum flexibility in creating specialization, sections allow plain text as well as
        phrase and block level elements. Because of the way XML grammars are defined within a DTD,
        any element that allows plain text cannot restrict the order or frequency of other elements.
        As a result, the <xmlelement class="+ topic/keyword markup-d/markupname xml-d/xmlelement " xtrc="xmlelement:4;22:38" xtrf="file:/C:/Git/dita/specification/common/reuse-w-lwdita/reuse-section.dita">section</xmlelement> element allows
          <xmlelement class="+ topic/keyword markup-d/markupname xml-d/xmlelement " xtrc="xmlelement:5;23:23" xtrf="file:/C:/Git/dita/specification/common/reuse-w-lwdita/reuse-section.dita">title</xmlelement> to appear anywhere as a child of
          <xmlelement class="+ topic/keyword markup-d/markupname xml-d/xmlelement " xtrc="xmlelement:6;24:23" xtrf="file:/C:/Git/dita/specification/common/reuse-w-lwdita/reuse-section.dita">section</xmlelement>. However, the intent of the specification is that
          <xmlelement class="+ topic/keyword markup-d/markupname xml-d/xmlelement " xtrc="xmlelement:7;25:23" xtrf="file:/C:/Git/dita/specification/common/reuse-w-lwdita/reuse-section.dita">title</xmlelement> should only be used once in any
          <xmlelement class="+ topic/keyword markup-d/markupname xml-d/xmlelement " xtrc="xmlelement:8;26:23" xtrf="file:/C:/Git/dita/specification/common/reuse-w-lwdita/reuse-section.dita">section</xmlelement>, and when used, it should precede any other text or
        element content.</note>
